BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Female Hormones) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (The Key Players) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 652.2 Td (Estrogen) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 636.2 Td (The primary female sex hormone responsible for reproductive development, bone health,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 622.2 Td (brain function, and cardiovascular health. Too much \(estrogen dominance\) or too little) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 608.2 Td (causes distinct symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 594.2 Td (- High estrogen: Heavy periods, breast tenderness, weight gain, mood swings) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 580.2 Td (- Low estrogen: Hot flashes, vaginal dryness, bone loss, brain fog) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 552.4 Td (Progesterone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.4 Td (The 'calming' hormone that balances estrogen, supports pregnancy, and promotes relaxation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.4 Td (and sleep.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 508.4 Td (- Low progesterone: Anxiety, insomnia, short cycles, spotting, infertility) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 480.6 Td (Testosterone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 464.6 Td (Women need small amounts for libido, muscle tone, energy, and motivation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 450.6 Td (- High testosterone \(PCOS\): Acne, facial hair, hair loss, irregular periods) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 436.6 Td (- Low testosterone: Low libido, fatigue, muscle weakness) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 408.8 Td (Cortisol) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 392.8 Td (The stress hormone that affects all other hormones when chronically elevated.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 378.8 Td (- High cortisol: Weight gain \(belly\), anxiety, insomnia, sugar cravings) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 351.0 Td (Thyroid Hormones \(T3, T4, TSH\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 335.0 Td (Control metabolism, energy, temperature regulation, and weight.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 321.0 Td (- Hypothyroid: Fatigue, weight gain, cold intolerance, hair loss, constipation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.0 Td (- Hyperthyroid: Weight loss, anxiety, heart palpitations, heat intolerance) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 279.2 Td (Insulin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 263.2 Td (Regulates blood sugar and is closely linked to all sex hormones.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 249.2 Td (- Insulin resistance: Weight gain, PCOS, sugar cravings, energy crashes) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 219.4 Td (The Menstrual Cycle Phases) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 197.4 Td (Phase 1: Menstrual \(Days 1-5\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 181.4 Td (All hormones are at their lowest. Energy is typically lowest. Focus on rest, gentle) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 167.4 Td (movement, and iron-rich foods.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 149.4 Td (Phase 2: Follicular \(Days 6-14\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 133.4 Td (Estrogen rises steadily. Energy increases, creativity peaks. Great time for new projects) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 119.4 Td (and intense exercise.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 101.4 Td (Phase 3: Ovulatory \(Days 15-17\)) Tj ET
endstream
