stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 6: Lifestyle & Supplement Strategies) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Stress Management for Hormones) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Chronic stress steals progesterone to make cortisol \(the 'progesterone steal'\).) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (- Morning cortisol management: Sunlight within 30 min of waking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Adaptogenic herbs: Ashwagandha, rhodiola, holy basil) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (- Evening routine: Dim lights, no screens, calming tea) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Say no: Overcommitment raises cortisol) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 570.4 Td (Exercise Guidelines) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 552.4 Td (- Avoid overexercising \(raises cortisol, disrupts hormones\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- PCOS: Mix of strength training and moderate cardio) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- Perimenopause: Prioritize strength training for bone/muscle) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- Thyroid issues: Avoid extreme exercise, focus on consistency) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 480.6 Td (Supplements to Discuss with Your Doctor) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 462.6 Td (- Magnesium glycinate: 200-400mg at bedtime) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 448.6 Td (- Vitamin D3: 2000-5000 IU \(test levels first\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 434.6 Td (- Omega-3 fish oil: 1000-2000mg EPA/DHA) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 420.6 Td (- B-complex: Supports overall hormone metabolism) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.6 Td (- Zinc: 15-30mg \(especially for PCOS\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 392.6 Td (- Inositol: 2-4g \(for PCOS insulin resistance\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 378.6 Td (- DIM: Supports healthy estrogen metabolism) Tj ET
endstream
