100 0 obj
<< /Length 2471 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: How long until I notice hormone improvements?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (Most women notice subtle improvements in 1-2 cycles. Significant changes typically take) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (3-6 months of consistent effort. Hormones respond slowly to lifestyle changes.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 618.4 Td (Q: Should I get my hormones tested?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (Yes, especially if symptoms are severe. Ask for: estrogen, progesterone \(Day 21\),) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (testosterone, DHEA-S, cortisol, full thyroid panel, fasting insulin, and vitamin D.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 560.6 Td (Q: Can I balance hormones without medication?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 544.6 Td (Many women can significantly improve symptoms through diet, lifestyle, and supplements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (alone. However, some conditions require medical intervention.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 502.8 Td (Q: Does birth control mask hormone problems?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 486.8 Td (Yes, hormonal birth control suppresses your natural cycle. It can mask underlying issues) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 472.8 Td (like PCOS or thyroid problems. Discuss alternatives with your doctor.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 445.0 Td (Q: What is seed cycling?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 429.0 Td (Eating specific seeds during different cycle phases: flax+pumpkin seeds in follicular) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 415.0 Td (phase, sesame+sunflower in luteal phase. Some women find it helpful for mild imbalances.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 387.2 Td (Q: How does weight affect hormones?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 371.2 Td (Fat tissue produces estrogen. Both excess weight and being underweight disrupt hormone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 357.2 Td (balance. Aim for a healthy weight through nourishing \(not restrictive\) eating.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 329.4 Td (Q: Can stress really stop my period?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313.4 Td (Yes. Extreme stress can cause hypothalamic amenorrhea by suppressing GnRH, the hormone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299.4 Td (that triggers ovulation. This is your body's protective mechanism.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 271.6 Td (Q: Is soy good or bad for hormones?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 255.6 Td (Moderate amounts of whole soy \(tempeh, edamame\) can be beneficial due to phytoestrogens.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 241.6 Td (Avoid processed soy isolates. Those with thyroid issues should monitor intake.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
